Manuel Ramil (born 8 March 1978 in Ares, A Coruña, Spain) is a Spanish musician, best known as the former keyboardist for the Power metal band WarCry and Torquemada and as the current keyboardist of alternative/power metal band Sauze, formed by himself, along with Alberto Ardines, Fernando Mon, and Toni Amboaje.
After going through several bands of unstable formation, in 1996 he formed the Heavy metal band Torquemada.
A year later he recorded his first EP, Santa Inquisición.
He remained in the band for almost 6 years but in September 2001 he left the band.
